shared_text:
Tri-County Fair Mtn. Grove MO
April 29 at 12:16 PM ·

Attention! We have some important information regarding the Tri-County Fair. We have had much discussion and have decided to change the dates for the fair, rather than cancel for the year. Our new dates are set for July 15-18, 2020. Next year we will go back to our usual week in June. Since we did not have a market animal weigh-in, market animals will only be weighed once at the fair. Exhibitors may sell 2 animals total in the market animal sale, each a different species. Maximum sale weights still apply.

This fair may look different than usual, but we are still excited to have one. We are taking sponsors to help in any way with the fair. Spread the word and see you in July!

post_text: The future is bright here at Norwood FFA. Greenhands and Officers attended the Statewide Greenhand Conference in West Plains in early January. This to shall pass....hang in there!

Missouri FFA Association
March 14 at 7:36 PM ·

Ag Ed/FFA Family,
In light of the current health issues and concerns resulting from the coronavirus (COVID-19), the State FFA Convention scheduled for April 23 and 24 is being postponed. Ag Ed staff members are working on a contingency plan for the State Convention program, State Leadership Development and State Career Development Events. My recommendation is that you reconsider holding all area and district FFA events involving significant numbers of students. While a variety of factors go into making a decision like this, be assured that the health and safety of our students and stakeholders is always our primary concern.

As an association we know there will be questions. We are evlauating all options as we move through the next few days and weeks. Continue to check with your advisor and watch social media.

Tri-County Fair Mtn. Grove MO
March 12, 2018 at 4:52 PM ·

ATTENTION EXHIBITORS!!
Be sure to mark your calendars for some important dates. The Tri-County Fair will take place June 6-9, 2018.

Market animal weigh in will be Sunday, April 22nd from 2-4 pm at the fairgrounds. There are not minimum weights for weigh in but there ARE maximum weights at the fair.
Those weights are as follows:
Beef steer 1350#
Lambs 150#
Goats 100#
Hogs 300#
Dairy steer 500#

NEW this year is a Dairy Steer class, maximum weights at sale time is 500#. These animals will sell at the market sale and WILL need to be at weigh-in in order to sell.

Tri-County Fair Scholarship Animal Essay Application

- Exhibitor Must be an In-Coming or Out-Going Sr.
- Must be enrolled in FFA, 4-H, or an Independent Jr. exhibiting at the 2017 Tri-County Fair.
- Must select species on application (Swine, Goat or Sheep)
- Animal MUST SELL at the Tri-County Fair.
- Animal & Grain Products are donated to the recipient (Grain donated By: MFA, Inc., Mountain Grove, MO)
- Monies raised by sale of animal will be issued directly to the school upon confirmed enrollment.
